{
  "message": "fix: update graph legend to show heatmap color scale when heatmap active\n\nThe legend overlay was hardcoded to always show status colors (Open,\nIn Progress, Closed, Blocked) even when heatmap mode was toggled on.\nNow conditionally displays a green-to-red gradient scale matching\ngetHeatmapColor() HSL range when heatmap is active, and shows the\nmetric name in the title.\n\nCloses #137\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>",
